data.name: dataGridViewPDFSOlder.ToolTip
data.value:
Drag the "older" PDF files into this list.
The list order indicates which "older" PDF is to be compared to which "newer" PDF. You can drag list items to reorder the list.
Doubleclick opens Explorer. Doubleclicking a list item opens Explorer at the folder for that item.

data.name: label1.ToolTip
data.value:
Setting the Output Printer:
1) Press the Windows default printer button and then set the default Windows printer to the printer you want the Output Printer to be.
2) Press the Set output printer button. The Output Printer will now be the default Windows printer.
This program will remember the printer setting. Upon closing, this program resets the default Windows printer back to what is was. You can also manually reset the default printer yourself after setting this program's Output Printer so that you have your normal default printer when using other applications while this application is busy working.

data.name: buttonWhatIsDefaultPrinter.ToolTip
data.value:
Your output printer selection will be saved for the next time you use this program.
The default Windows printer resets back to what it was before starting this program. That happens when this program quits.
You can also manually reset the default printer yourself after setting this program's Output Printer so that you have your normal default printer when using other applications while this application is busy working.

data.value:
The difference images are at the "newers" folder. Doubleclick the Newers list to open that folder.
There will be two files for each difference image.
One is a PNG and the other is a PDF of that PNG.
The PDF of that PNG is for file viewing convenience.
The PNG is used to make the preview image below.

data.name: checkBoxCleanUp.ToolTip
data.value:
This option is for diagnostic purposes. You probably want to keep this option checked.
The process involves creating intermeadiate PNG files. These are deleted when the process completes. Unchecking this skips their deletion.

data.name: maskedTextBoxBlackFuzz.ToolTip
data.value:
Fuzz value percent applied to black for newer PDFs
Black items on the newer PDFs are converted to red color. The same items on the older PDFs will cover the newer red items. Totally new almost black items on the newer PDFs will not be red as they should unless there is some fuzz in deciding what is black that should be turned red. A value of 75% black fuzz is good for turning most drawing grayshades to red.

data.name: maskedTextBoxWhiteFuzz.ToolTip
data.value:
Fuzz value percent applied to white for the older PDFs.
White is assumed to be the background color that is the blank paper. White is turned to transparent in the older PDFs, which are then overlayed on top of the newer PDFs so that the newer PDFs show through except where the older PDFs are not transparent. Sometimes the older PDFs are not totally white in the blank paper area. The white fuzz value allows for the almost white blank paper backgound to be also changed to transparent. The white fuzz is normally 00%. Increase it to 50% if needed.
